column2: After a heavy weekend of boating.
Algae just starting to bloom in shallow water but fishing and swimming still okay.  The water color is greenish brown.
The water color is greenish brown.
Algae level much less compared to two to four weeks ago.
A couple of rain storms this past week have made the water cloudy.  Lake level up about 2".
Rain in previous week.  The water is greenish brown.
Clear all week.  Rain runoff effects water clarity much.  The water is greenish brown.
Mild algae bloom in some areas of the lake.  The water color is greenish brown.
Minor algae bloom in some areas of the lake.
Level up about 5" since last report.
Overcast- windy- heavy rain night before
Loons- osprey- ducks- beaver- otter present- poor fishing
Highest water level in many years
Heavy rains all week.  Lake level: very high
Sunny day- water still- very cold.
Heavy rain all week long.  Loons have 1 chick.  Mallard has 7 little ducklings.
More weed growth than in past years.  Moderate algal bloom.
I would be interested in monitoring other data for this lake- i.e. dissolved oxygen- pH- PO4e- NO2-- etc.  If you need that information. (sent note to Laura 6/13/95-cvh)
Bright sunshine- loons have one chick.
Warm- sunny + dry all week long.
Heavy overcast- rain last night.  Loon chick doing well.
Clear and cool- sunny.  Otters on the lake- but haven't seen the loons.
Beautiful weather.  Mosquitoes doing extremely well.  Loon still sitting on her egg.
Heavy rain yesterday.  Lake level still very high.
Hazy sunshine- no rain for about a week.
Bright sunshine- beautiful day.  Loons have two chicks that just hatched.
Lake clarity is much better than is has been over the summer
Heavy rain earlier in the week.
Sunny- very windy.  15' sample had some bottom muck.     Sunny and very windy.  Clumps of floating algae seen in the lake.  Adult loons and 2 chicks still doing well.
Sunny- windy- heavy rain previous week.
Water level highest I've seen in 25 years.
Windy and sunny.  Loons have one chick.
Appears to be an algea bloom this year.
Bright sunshine- calm- and rain yesterday.
Very windy; slightly overcast.  Lake level very high.
Windy and sunny.  Very heavy rain 2 days ago.  Lake
Sunny- windy and mighty cold - brrrrrrr
cool and sunny- a beautiful day
Overcast.  Loons have one chick - doing well.
Water looks clearer than earlier in the summer
2" of rain in the past week
Loons have 2 healthy chicks.  Partly cloudy and breezy.  Lots of rain in the past 2 weeks.  Bass fishing has been great.
Clear- sunny and calm.  Very low water level
Over 3" of rain in the past 2 weeks.  Lake level still very low.  Loons and one chick still doing well.
Beautiful! Sunny and calm. Extremely low water level.
Sunny- calm- water level still going down
Sunny- light breeze- water level still very low
Over 4" of rain in the past week.
Very little rain in the past 2 weeks
Very little rain in the past 2 weeks.
Cloudy but not too windy.  Very cold.  Almost froze my fingers collecting D.O. samples.  Ice off 4/25/08 observed by Don Morrell.
Windy and sunny.  Heavy rain(5") previous week.
Bright and sunny.  Water was calm.  Water level very low for this time of year.
Windy and overcast.  1" rain in the past week.
Sunny and calm.  No rain in the past week.  Water level still extremely low.
Weather sunny and calm.  Water level extremely low.
15 foot sample unavailable due to low lake water levels
Sunny and windy.  Lake level very low.  Some bottom sediment in 15' DO sample due to low lake level.
Sunny and windy.  Heavy rain in previous week

Another 4" of rain in the past 2 weeks.  Lake level is as high as I have ever seen in the past 20 years.  Loons had a nest and laid 2 eggs but abandoned it before the eggs hatched.  Only one loon is seen on the lake now.

Sunny and calm; a beautiful day.  We were hit by the April 10th tornado.  Many broken trees along the shore.  Fortunately no one was injured.  Ice out was April 22nd.  Lake level has come up some with recent rains- but is still somewhat low for this time of year. Sunny and calm; a beautiful day.  We were hit by the April 10th tornado.  Many broken trees along the shore.  Fortunately no one was injured.  Ice out was April 22nd.  Lake level has come up some with recent rains- but is still somewhat low for this time of year.  This is the highest dissolved oxygen measurements that I have ever seen.
Bright sunshine- but very windy.  Lake level is up about 12" from the last entry due to heavy rain in the past 3 weeks.
Overcast and slight wind.  Little rain in the past two weeks.  Lake level down somewhat.
Eagle flying over the lake.  Sunny but windy.  Lake level down about 10" from high water level this summer.
Cold and cloudy with a light wind.  Ice off was 3/20/12.  One loon observed on the lake.
Both loons are now on the lake
Cloudy and windy.  2.75" of rain last week.  Loon on the nest with 2 eggs.

Light wind.  Heavy rain in the past week.   Loon pair and 2 chicks doing fine.  One of the adult loons had become entangled in fishing line last weekend.  Adult loons were banded by DNR this past week.

Sunny and fairly windy.  Lots of boating activity on the lake this weekend.  Loons and chicks still doing well.  Remarkable change in water temperature and dissolved oxygen since the last testing one month ago.

Bright sunshine but windy.  Fishing pretty slow yet until water warms up a bit.  Loon pair seen swimming close to shore probably looking for a good nesting site.  Water level the highest it has been in quite a few years.
Two loon chicks were hatched in the previous week.  Both seem to be doing well.
Sunny but very windy.  Clumps of floating algae on parts of the lake.  Adults and 2 loon chicks doing well.
Secchi reading to correspond with satellite reading.  Heavy overcast with a little fog.
Sunny and light wind.  Loons have one chick who appears to be doing very well.
Cloudy with light wind.  Two loons observed on the lake; 1 adult and 1 chick.  Heavy rain recently.
Heavy overcast with a slight breeze.
Sunny with a light wind.  Only one loon sporadically seen on the lake during the week.
Hot and sunny.  Very calm water.  Only one loon observed on the lake.
Hazy clouds and windy.  Heard loons on the lake
Sunny- clear day. 69 degrees. Slight breeze from northeast.
Beautiful- calm- clear day. Single loon on the lake.
Partly sunny- 68 degrees- fairly windy- wind from the north- single loon
Overcast- 64 degrees- slight breeze from the west- about 5 mph. Haven't seen the loons in a few days.
Beautiful- sunny morning--clear- 63 degrees; west wind 5 to 10 mph.
Beautiful- clear day. 71 degrees- wind 7 MPH NW. No loons today.
Light rain- strong west wind- 12 mph- air temperature 56 degrees
Clear- sunny- calm day. Didn't see the loon today.
Overcast- windy; eagle flying overhead- patrolling the lake. Wind 12 mph NNW. 3.5 inches of rain over the last three days.
